    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2691: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-16T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 16, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 16—6:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>219. The … and … Ministers both have called upon me to advise me that they have
                    cabled their Governments a strong recommendation against exercising further
                    pressure at Geneva upon Japan. This appears to be virtually the unanimous
                    judgment here of foreign diplomats of all countries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
